cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with developing computational models for musical taste dynamics, which involves analyzing a large dataset on internet radio station creation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these, cs.SD and cs.IR seem to be the most likely sub-categories, as they directly relate to the domain of music and information retrieval, respectively. However, the paper also involves developing a model utilizing recurrent neural networks, which falls under the purview of cs.LG. Additionally, the paper deals with the complexities of the domain and identifies unique challenges, which could be relevant to cs.SI. Finally, the paper applies the model to the problem of next station prediction, which involves natural language processing and could be relevant to cs.CL.
